content.p:
W had not received a draft of the article in the Director magazine prior to publication

W has produced an email dated 19 July 2012 from a third party who dealt with public relations on behalf of B Ltd.  Whilst it was suggested to her that this email appeared to show that she had been sent a draft of the article in order that she could approve the contents prior to publication, I am satisfied that W was truthful when she told me that the (published) magazine had been sent to her in order that she could disseminate it to a targeted audience as part of the campaign to publicise the company.  
